MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1107364619}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a2b5acffb403c434e91edf4a65b03ddc, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::News_Manager
  newsTxt: {fileID: 1570598961}
  News:
  - 'Spice Markets Surge: Spice prices hit record highs as Galactic Empire officials
    allegedly trade Arrakis stockpiles for exclusive Mustafar thermal spa memberships. '
  - 'Tourism Warning: A group of tourists on Pandora was hospitalized yesterday after
    mistaking a highly toxic bioluminescent fungus for glowing candy. '
  - 'Bifrost Brawls: Odin declares a temporary ban on mead imports to Asgard after
    a drunken tavern brawl damaged a significant portion of the Rainbow Bridge. '
  - 'Lock Your Ships: Sector Gamma authorities warn scavengers on Titan to secure
    their vessels, as local monsters have reportedly learned how to hotwire standard
    escape pods. '
  - 'Temporal Glitch: The Gallifreyan temporal council apologizes for the recent
    "Tuesday loop." Citizens are advised to just relax and enjoy the extra 24 hours
    of weekend. '
  - 'Import Disaster: UAC scientists on Mars attempted to import cooling water from
    4546-B, accidentally releasing a Leviathan-class predator into the lava-filtration
    system. '
  - 'Health Alert: A new strain of the "Bounce-Fever" virus is sweeping the Mushroom
    Planet; symptoms include uncontrollable giggling and an urge to stomp on turtles. '
  - 'Expeditions Halted: Tours to Paradise have been temporarily suspended after
    visitors complained that the colossal stone statues "kept judging their outfit
    choices." '
  - 'Labor Strike: Alazmec workers on Mustafar are striking for better air conditioning,
    claiming their current breakroom feels "slightly warmer than the actual lava." '
  - 'Extreme Sports: Sandworm surfing is now officially classified as a lethal sport
    on Arrakis; tourists must sign a 400-page waiver before approaching the deep
    dunes. '
  - 'Cross-Sector Tournament: Asgardian gods have officially challenged the monsters
    of Titan to a glorious battle tournament. Tickets are selling out across all
    three Sectors! '
  - 'Marine Biology: Deep-sea researchers on 4546-B have discovered a new species
    of Peeper fish that appears to communicate entirely through sarcastic blinking. '
  - 'Diplomatic Blunder: Time Lords accidentally vetoed a peace treaty before it
    was even proposed, causing mild temporal confusion and very awkward apologies. '
  - 'Audio Hack: Anarchic factions on Mars have successfully hacked the main UAC
    intercoms, blasting heavy metal music 24/7 across all residential hab-blocks. '
  - 'Botanical Breakthrough: Na''vi botanists successfully cross-pollinated Pandora
    flora with spores from the Mushroom Planet, resulting in glowing, highly bouncy
    trees. '
  - 'Weather Update: Sector Alpha experiences a rare cosmic heatwave. Mustafar reports
    no change, while Arrakis moisture farmers demand immediate galactic subsidies. '
  - 'Scrap Market Crash: Scrap metal prices plummet as terrified scavengers on Titan
    flood the market with mysteriously abandoned, slightly blood-stained flashlights. '
  - 'Fringe Theories: Conspiracy theorists now claim the ancient Engineer architectures
    on Paradise are actually just giant vending machines waiting for the right cosmic
    coin. '
  - 'Transit Dispute: Gallifreyan diplomats accuse Asgard of using "primitive magic"
    after a TARDIS gets stuck halfway through the Bifrost transport beam. '
  - 'Allergy Season: "Spice-sneezes" are on the rise among tourists on Arrakis. Locals
    advise wearing a mask unless you want to accidentally see through time. '
  - 'Launchpad Delays: All flights out of Sector Beta are currently delayed due to
    a massive migration of sentient mushrooms blocking the main orbital runways.'
  chosedNews:
  - 
  - 
  - 
